cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  Hi Everyone and welcome to today's Precision Club session, in which the plan is that we'll be looking at sequences over a 1NT Openings. 

 If you have not already done so, please have a look at the notes I have prepared on Precision Club bidding.

You can find these on: ^*hhttp://ocp.pigpen.org.uk^*n  

In particular, you might want to have the 1NT Page up on view during the session: ^*hhttp://ocp.pigpen.org.uk/1n.php^*n


|fp|t-title|at|The  1 NT  Opening|fp||at|

The topic today is not exactly "Precision-specific" in that what I'm going to deal with could apply equally to ACOL, Standard American, 2/1 or any other system.

Consequently, don't be afraid to sit and play if you're not yet "into" Precision, although the example hands do assume a Variable 1NT Opening 10-12 non-vul and 13-15 vul, because that is what our Precision system uses.

Similarly, the scheme of responses that you play over a Precision Opening 1NT bid does not really affect any part of the system, and so you are free to use whatever scheme of responses you like.

What I am going to show you today is simply my preferred scheme.
|
