cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  In standard Precision Club, 1NT is opened with any hand containing 13-15 points which is either: 

4432, 4333 or 5332 shape with a 5-card MINOR (NOT a Major).

Like the 1@D and 2@C Openings, the precision 1NT Opening specifically DENIES holding a 5-card Major, but I'll come back to that in a minute.
^k|ih|SaT9HT54DA872CAT9|at|

|ht|h|at|^c@2So this hand is a perfectly  
okay non-vulnerable 1NT Opening 
(if a bit less than ideal).
^b@2^^^^
A 1NT Opening is HUGELY preemptive, however, so in the system I play we use a VARIABLE 1NT Opening 
^c@210-12  when we're NOT vulnerable and 
13-15  when we   ARE vulnerable.

^b@21@D is used to Open Balanced hands that do NOT qualify for a 1NT Opening because of vulnerability/point range
^c@213-15  when NOT vulnerable, and 
11-12  when Vulnerable.

^b@2Please note that we do  NOT  open 10-point  balanced hands when vulnerable. 


In practice, you can play any strength No Trump you like with Precision, but if the top of your No Trump range is higher than 15 points, it does affect the requirements for your 1@C Opening.

Some Precision pairs, for example, use a 14-16 1NT so for them a 1@C Opening is 17+ if balanced.
|
