The key to transfers is the extra round of bidding that they generate.

Since you ask partner to bid your suit for you, you can use this mechanism with ANY hand with a 5-card or longer suit, whatever strength, and then pass, invite, force, show a second suit, bid No Trumps, or whatever, as appropriate.

My advice, for what it's worth, is that I would pretty much ALWAYS transfer into a 5-card Major, even if semi-balanced.

The only time I would perhaps pause for thought is a completely honourless 5-card suit in a semi-balanced hand with scattered values outside.

Where Minors are concerned, I would normally only bother to transfer into a Minor if it was a 6-card suit and I was weak or at least slam-invitational. 

^*bOR^*n  if I had a game-going hand with a 4-card Major AS WELL.  If I was transferring into 3@C or 3@D and intending to rebid 3NT afterwards, I might as well just bid 3NT straightaway if only interested in game.


